{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-03942/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-03942"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:39:42"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["One woman glares at the other before speaking."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-03942","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-03942"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1/9b2f9543-8ac6-4ccc-89bd-4974f6afde62","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:53:01.166Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In an interview with <em>Empire</em>, PTA spoke about shooting on location rather than on a soundstage: “It probably would have ended up being exactly the same, but I think what you get is a lot of little details that you wouldn't have gotten, like just the way the floorboards creak, the way that the handles on the doorknobs... The way things sound is probably the biggest thing that you get that the greatest sound designer in the world couldn't come up with. You'd be manufacturing stuff, and you'd be off the mark somehow... The other real thing was life outside the windows, which [with a] sound stage you would have to normally... people would do a green screen or a backdrop or something like that, but we actually had Fitzroy Square right outside there...You put a few people in hats and costumes and have them walk around... That is a kind of an extra layer of reality or pretend reality” (Xixax TV, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW88222089 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rdEDLwX49cY\"><u>PHANTOM THREAD - AUDIO - Paul Thomas Anderson interviewed on the Empire podcast</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-03942/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:80.10767160161504,62.58411843876182,500.0269179004039,260.9959623149395"}}}]}]}]}